<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n10096a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10096a">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10096a"> 96(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> exemplary</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Cette ordonnance du 13 d&eacute;cembre 1623 d&eacute;fendait &agrave; toutes personnes autres que les ma&icirc;tres de Postes de fournir des chevaux aux courriers et voyageurs &eacute;trangers circulant dans le royaume, sous peine de 500 &eacute;cus d&apos;amende pour la premi&egrave;re contravention. En cas de r&eacute;cidive, les d&eacute;linquants devaient &ecirc;tre punis <mark>exemplairement</mark>. Cet adverbe donne &agrave; penser. <font color="green">[This ordinance of 13 December 1623 forbade all people other than postmasters to provide horses for couriers and foreign voyagers travelling throughout the kingdom, under penalty of a 500 ecu fine for the first infraction. In case of relapse, the punishment for delinquents was to be &lsquo;exemplary&rsquo;&mdash;an adjective that gives one pause for thought.]</font> <small> Arthur de Rothschild, <a name="ARHD" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#ARHD"><cite title="source">Histoire de la poste</cite></a> (1876) 161</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: See <a name="n10096c" href="n10all.htm#n10096c">N10 (VI.B.16):096(c)</a> below. </mm> </dd></dl>
